{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"I made a steampunk costume","content":"<p>Every couple of years I actively participate in our version of mardi gras and dress up in a costume. It&#8217;s usually something mundane like dressing up as a living statue or a girl or whatever.</p>\n<div style=\"width: 360px\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><img class=\" \" title=\"Full costume\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzud2o2A4V1qekjngo1_5003.jpg\" alt=\"Full costume\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Full costume</p></div>\n<p>This year, however, I decided to go full out. Finally, an excuse to make a steampunk costume!</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m not the handiest person in the world so the whole thing was a bit of a mess &#8211; not a single straight cut anywhere, parts of my room are now gold and there is trash everywhere. But I had a lot of fun working manually for two days. It&#8217;s remarkably refreshing to do something in meatspace now and anon.</p>\n<p>All the manly work even made my fifth chest hair grow! Score!</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m quite pleased with the result, the costume turned out pretty decent and only cost about 30 euro in parts and another ~300 euro in time. Plus whatever old crap I found collecting dust around the house; like for instance, bits of my high school death metal outfit.</p>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"It begins with a pile of junk\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzpj40CCuq1qekjngo1_5005.jpg\" alt=\"It begins with a pile of junk\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">It begins with a pile of junk</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"Regular welding glasses from a store, just added the fluff\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzpnlcFYDv1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"Regular welding glasses from a store, just added the fluff\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Regular welding glasses from a store, just added the fluff</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"First stage of shoulder armor - an old belt, strip of cloth and leather tied on with aluminium wire\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzpv4nKIQy1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"First stage of shoulder armor - an old belt, strip of cloth and leather tied on with aluminium wire\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">First stage of shoulder armor - an old belt, strip of cloth and leather tied on with aluminium wire</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"The hat is actually something I always wear\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzqox0thrJ1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"The hat is actually something I always wear\" width=\"500\" height=\"669\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The hat is actually something I always wear</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3730\" style=\"width: 624px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-3730 \" title=\"Normal welding gloves and some wire\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo1-1024x764.jpg\" alt=\"Normal welding gloves and some wire\" width=\"614\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo1-1024x764.jpg 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo1-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Normal welding gloves and some wire</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3731\" style=\"width: 624px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-13.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-3731 \" title=\"Took several tries to make symmetric wings\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-13-1024x764.jpg\" alt=\"Took several tries to make symmetric wings\" width=\"614\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-13-1024x764.jpg 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-13-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Took several tries to make symmetric wings</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"The trick is to apply copper paint with a sponge\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzqwrcTn2l1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"The trick is to apply copper paint with a sponge\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The trick is to apply copper paint with a sponge</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"Armor panels\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzr07u1kEI1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"Armor panels\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Armor panels</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"The finished shoulder armor drying \" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzr4m789651qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"The finished shoulder armor drying \" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The finished shoulder armor drying</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"The gloves turned out quite well\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzr80yr3Lq1qekjngo1_5004.jpg\" alt=\"The gloves turned out quite well\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The gloves turned out quite well</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3733\" style=\"width: 545px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-22.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-3733 \" title=\"Manliest my desk has ever looked\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-22-764x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Manliest my desk has ever looked\" width=\"535\" height=\"717\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-22-764x1024.jpg 764w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/photo-22-224x300.jpg 224w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 535px) 100vw, 535px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Manliest my desk has ever looked</p></div>\n<div style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img title=\"Slightly bigger picture of full outfit\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/tumblr_lzud2o2A4V1qekjngo1_5003.jpg\" alt=\"Slightly bigger picture of full outfit\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Slightly bigger picture of full outfit</p></div>\n<p>Unfortunately the costume did not prevent me from accidentally getting way too drunk at the party. Lost my real glasses, the hat, my keys, even my moleskine.</p>\n<p>All in all, the most expensive party I&#8217;ve ever been to &#8230; but at least the costume is cool ðŸ™‚</p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.winextra.com/2012/02/your-nerf-rifle-love-just-got-seriously-steampunked/\">Your NERF rifle love just got seriously steampunked</a> (winextra.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://geeks.thedailywh.at/2012/02/22/steampunk-nerf-gun-of-the-day/\">Steampunk Nerf Gun of the Day</a> (geeks.thedailywh.at)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://darkrosedesign.com/2012/02/15/steampunk-costume-update/\">Steampunk Costume Update</a> (darkrosedesign.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://mishidems.wordpress.com/2012/02/21/blast-from-the-past-steampunk/\">Blast from the Past: Steampunk</a> (mishidems.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://kasiajames.wordpress.com/2012/01/25/steampunk-moves-on/\">Steampunk moves on</a> (kasiajames.wordpress.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://geektyrant.com/news/2011/12/19/awesome-steampunkd-disney-character-art.html\">Awesome Steampunk&#8217;d Disney Character Art!</a> (geektyrant.com)</li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://laughingsquid.com/the-steampunk-worlds-fair-2012/\">The Steampunk World&#8217;s Fair 2012</a> (laughingsquid.com)</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; height: 15px;\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none; float: right;\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=16f65399-a0a0-445f-a88d-a612c62a3c13\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" /></a></div>\n"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Swizec Blog","subtitle":"Fetch Data From Local WP Install"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"086604c7-4685-538f-80d5-60e847882ea4"}}